metadata.name: No Fly Zone
metadata.description:
Title: No Fly Zone

Photographer: Photox

Edition: 1/1

Story: If you've ever been up in a hot air balloon, you'll be able to relate to the feeling of effortlessly drifting through the sky. This photo is the result of what happens when the wind unexpectedly changes, and you end up drifting through the No Fly Zone above the Australian Parliament House. This area is restricted for all types of aircraft including drones, so I made the most of the circumstances and captured this image from an angle that is rarely seen.

High resolution version available to asset owner
